# Build, Run, Test

Java 21 + Apache Ant. No Maven/Gradle; dependencies are vendored jars in `oem/`.
Run all commands from the **repo root** (data paths are relative to the CWD).

## Build

```bash
ant compile   # -> build/classes (engine) and build/default/classes (campaign)
ant clean     # remove build/
```

`ant` (default `dist`) builds zipped distributions and needs launch4j/jre config -
prefer `ant compile` for normal work.

## Run

Game:
```bash
java -cp build/classes:build/default/classes:oem/jorbis/jorbis0.0.17.jar:oem/gson/gson-2.8.6.jar:oem/java-vorbis-support/java-vorbis-support-1.2.1.jar mclachlan.maze.game.Launcher
```

Editor:
```bash
java -cp build/classes:build/default/classes:oem/jorbis/jorbis0.0.17.jar:oem/gson/gson-2.8.6.jar:oem/java-vorbis-support/java-vorbis-support-1.2.1.jar mclachlan.maze.editor.swing.SwingEditor
```

Needs a display (AWT/Swing). Config in `maze.cfg` / `user.cfg`.

## Testing

There is **no JUnit suite**. `*Test*` classes (e.g. under `maze/test/`,
`jgpgoap/`, `crusader/client/`) are standalone `main()` harnesses run by hand.
Validate by compiling with `ant compile` and launching where feasible.
